<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#DAF7A6">
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">
    <RelativeLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:padding="16dp"
        tools:context=".HydroponicPlantActivity">

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView"
            android:layout_width="200dp"
            android:layout_height="200dp"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:src="@drawable/grape" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/nutrientsTextView"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/imageView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:fontFamily="sans-serif-medium"
            android:text="Nutrients from Plant:

Grapes require essential macronutrients (nitrogen, phosphorus, potassium) and micronutrients (calcium, magnesium, iron, etc.) for healthy growth. Hydroponically, a balanced nutrient solution is essential to support grapevine growth, fruiting, and ripening."
            android:textColor="#070707"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/growingDurationTextView"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/nutrientsTextView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:text="Plant Growing Duration:

The growth duration for hydroponic grapevines can vary depending on the specific grape variety, environmental conditions, and the hydroponic system used. Traditional grapevines can take several years to bear fruit, but with optimal conditions and the right varieties, you might start seeing grapes within 2-3 years."
            android:textColor="#070707"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/diseaseTextView"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/growingDurationTextView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:text="Diseases Occurring During Growth:

Grapes can be susceptible to various diseases, including:

Powdery mildew and downy mildew: These fungal diseases can affect grapevines, especially in conditions of high humidity. Proper humidity control is essential in hydroponics to prevent these diseases.

Pests like grape phylloxera: They can attack grape roots, but in a hydroponic system, this issue is less likely to occur."
            android:textColor="#070707"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <Button
            android:id="@+id/fertilizersTextView"
            android:layout_width="129dp"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_below="@id/diseaseTextView"
            android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
            android:background="@drawable/button_background"
            android:text="Buy Nutrition"
            android:textColor="#ffff"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

    </RelativeLayout>
    </ScrollView>


</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>